Danielle Ockwell, whose superior was Lord and who had asked for a child protection training because she was concerned about his behaviour, said that the child service director Jacqui Barnat, who was the chief of the YMCA Caringbah, was "very intimidating and most of the time very inaccessible."
The Managing Director stated that he would not accept statements from employees that they would not have been able to report to their superiors.
Instead, he said, rather, her friendship with Lord has affected her judgment, which is why they did not report him.
Hare said that he had informed the board of the YMCA NSW that the lesson that the organization had to draw from the "Jonathan Lord incident" was "not the reporting" by employees, and the board had agreed to it.
